Program: The Documentary
Title: All that Stands in the Way
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01v5sr7
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 23 Mar 2014
Around the world young women still lack the same opportunities as men, despite most countries legislating against gender discrimination. So, what are the entrenched social and cultural attitudes that stand in the way of girls achieving equality? Through personal and informal accounts of the lives of teenage girls in Iceland, London, Lesotho, and Amman, Ros Atkins considers what freedom looks like to these women and how the language of gender can stand in their way. (Picture: Mira (left) and her sister Rezan who live in Amman in Jordan) Show less